g/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"240,000\"><mn>240,000</mn></math>. Substituting&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"300\"><mn>300</mn></math> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"240,000\"><mn>240,000</mn></math> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi></math> in the equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals a left parenthesis 2 right parenthesis Superscript StartFraction x Over 75 EndFraction\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>75</mn></mfrac></msup></math> yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"240,000 equals a left parenthesis 2 right parenthesis Superscript StartFraction 300 Over 75 EndFraction\"><mn>240,000</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mfrac><mn>300</mn><mn>75</mn></mfrac></msup></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"240,000 equals a left parenthesis 2 right parenthesis Superscript 4\"><mn>240,000</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mn>4</mn></msup></math>, which is equivalent to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"240,000 equals a left parenthesis 16 right parenthesis\"><mn>240,000</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>)</mo></math>. Dividing both sides of this equation by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"16\"><mn>16</mn></math> yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"15,000 equals a\"><mn>15,000</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi></math>. Therefore, the population of this town in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"1659\"><mn>1659</mn></math> was <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"15,000\"><mn>15,000</mn></math>.</p>"